zhnLANDevice.name: zhnLANDevice

revisions.description: Added new lanEthernetInterfaceConfigTable objects: zhnDhcpConditionalServingPoolObjects Added new zhnIpInterfaceTableobject naptEnabled

Added new lanEthernetInterfaceConfigTable objects: lanEthernetLanFollowsWan lanEthernetIgmpPriorityMark lanEthernetIgmpPvid Added new zhnIpInterfaceTable object: alternateWanIfName Added new lanHostConfigManagementTable objects: zhnUseWanVlan zhnEnableStaticLease
Added the following objects: lanEthAclRulesTable lanDefaultIfName lanDefaultIfIpAddress lanEthernetAcl lanEthernetAclRulesNumberofEntries igmpGroupQuerier
Fixed MIB tree and table indices. Also added lanEthIntfStatisticsTable.
Added pppoeConfigTable for configuring PPPoE LAN Host configuration parameters and lanEthernetRateLimitTable for configuring rate limits for LAN Ethernet Devices.

zhnLANDevice.description: This file defines the private Enterprise MIB extensions that define LAN ethernet interface related objects supported by the Zhone CPEs.

LANEthernetStatusValues.name: LANEthernetStatusValues
LANEthernetStatusValues.description: Ethernet LAN interface status. An enumeration of: Up NoLink Error Disabled

LANEthernetMaxBitRateValues.name: LANEthernetMaxBitRateValues
LANEthernetMaxBitRateValues.description: The maximum upstream and downstream bit rate available to this connection. Enumeration of: 10 100 1000 Auto

LANEthernetDuplexModeValues.name: LANEthernetDuplexModeValues
LANEthernetDuplexModeValues.description: The duplex mode available to this connection. Enumeration of: Half Full Auto

LANEthernetPauseModeValues.name: LANEthernetPauseModeValues
LANEthernetPauseModeValues.description: The pause mode available to this connection. Enumeration of: Auto Enable Disable

IPInterfaceAddressingTypeValues.name: IPInterfaceAddressingTypeValues
IPInterfaceAddressingTypeValues.description: The addressing method used to assign the LAN-side IP Address. Enumeration of: Unknown Unconfigured Default DHCP Static PPPoE

DNSTypeValues.name: DNSTypeValues
DNSTypeValues.description: Enumeration of: Default - Get the DNS information from the uplink interface Static - The DNS information is manually provisioned DHCP - The DNS information is obtained via DHCP

IpPppoeConnectionTypeValues.name: IpPppoeConnectionTypeValues
IpPppoeConnectionTypeValues.description: Enumeration of: IP_Routed IP_Bridged PPPoE_IP_Routed PPPoE_IP_Bridged Unconfigured

PPPUserConnectionRequestValues.name: PPPUserConnectionRequestValues
PPPUserConnectionRequestValues.description: Enumeration of: None Down Up Connect Disconnect

PPPAuthenticationProtocolValues.name: PPPAuthenticationProtocolValues
PPPAuthenticationProtocolValues.description: Enumeration of: AUTO_AUTH PAP CHAP MS-CHAP

WANPppConnectionStatusValues.name: WANPppConnectionStatusValues
WANPppConnectionStatusValues.description: Enumeration of: Unconfigured Connecting Authenticating Connected PendingDisconnect Disconnecting Disconnected

WANPppLastConnectionErrorValues.name: WANPppLastConnectionErrorValues
WANPppLastConnectionErrorValues.description: Enumeration of: ERROR_NONE ERROR_ISP_TIME_OUT ERROR_COMMAND_ABORTED ERROR_NOT_ENABLED_FOR_INTERNET ERROR_BAD_PHONE_NUMBER ERROR_USER_DISCONNECT ERROR_ISP_DISCONNECT ERROR_IDLE_DISCONNECT ERROR_FORCED_DISCONNECT ERROR_SERVER_OUT_OF_RESOURCES ERROR_RESTRICTED_LOGON_HOURS ERROR_ACCOUNT_DISABLED ERROR_ACCOUNT_EXPIRED ERROR_PASSWORD_EXPIRED ERROR_AUTHENTICATION_FAILURE ERROR_NO_DIALTONE ERROR_NO_CARRIER ERROR_NO_ANSWER ERROR_LINE_BUSY ERROR_UNSUPPORTED_BITSPERSECOND ERROR_TOO_MANY_LINE_ERRORS ERROR_IP_CONFIGURATION ERROR_UNKNOWN

LANEthernetAclValues.name: LANEthernetAclValues
LANEthernetAclValues.description: The access list values available to an ethernet interface. Enumeration of: Disable BlackList WhiteList Unsupported

LANEthernetIpProtocolValues.name: LANEthernetIpProtocolValues
LANEthernetIpProtocolValues.description: The access list IP protocol values with which to filter. Enumeration of: tcp(1) udp(2) icmp(3) igmp(4) any(5)

lanDeviceTable.name: lanDeviceTable
lanDeviceTable.description: Table of LAN devices, including Ethernet, WLAN, and USB physical interfaces

lanDeviceEntry.name: lanDeviceEntry
lanDeviceEntry.description: Table of LAN devices, including Ethernet, WLAN, and USB physical interfaces. Each instance contains all LAN-related objects for a given bridged subnet.

lanEthernetInterfaceNumberOfEntries.name: lanEthernetInterfaceNumberOfEntries
lanEthernetInterfaceNumberOfEntries.description: Number of instances of lanEthernetInterfaceConfig entries for this LAN device.

lanUSBInterfaceNumberOfEntries.name: lanUSBInterfaceNumberOfEntries
lanUSBInterfaceNumberOfEntries.description: Number of instances of lanUSBInterfaceConfig entries for this LAN device.

lanWLANConfigurationNumberOfEntries.name: lanWLANConfigurationNumberOfEntries
lanWLANConfigurationNumberOfEntries.description: Number of instances of lanWLANInterfaceConfig entries for this LAN device.

lanMocaInterfaceNumberOfEntries.name: lanMocaInterfaceNumberOfEntries
lanMocaInterfaceNumberOfEntries.description: Number of instances of lanMocaInterfaceConfig entries for this LAN device.

igmpSnoopingCfgTable.name: igmpSnoopingCfgTable
igmpSnoopingCfgTable.description: Table of IGMP configuration information for LAN devices, including Ethernet, WLAN, and USB physical interfaces

igmpSnoopingCfgEntry.name: igmpSnoopingCfgEntry
igmpSnoopingCfgEntry.description: Table of IGMP configuration information for LAN devices, including Ethernet, WLAN, and USB physical interfaces.

igmpEnable.name: igmpEnable
igmpEnable.description: Enables or disables IGMP snooping for the LAN device.

igmpMode.name: igmpMode
igmpMode.description: IGMP Snooping mode. Enumeration of: Standard Blocking

igmpIfName.name: igmpIfName
igmpIfName.description: The interface name for this LAN device. This object has the same value as the ipInterfaceifName object in the ipInterfaceTable and is included within the IGMP table for convenience purposes.

lanHostConfigManagementTable.name: lanHostConfigManagementTable
lanHostConfigManagementTable.description: Table of LAN Host Configuration Management information for LAN devices, including Ethernet, WLAN, and USB physical interfaces

lanHostConfigManagementEntry.name: lanHostConfigManagementEntry
lanHostConfigManagementEntry.description: Table of LAN Host Configuration Management information for LAN devices, including Ethernet, WLAN, and USB physical interfaces

dhcpServerConfigurable.name: dhcpServerConfigurable
dhcpServerConfigurable.description: Enables the configuration of the DHCP server on the LAN interface If this variable is set to false, the CPE should restore its default DHCP server settings.

zhnDhcpServerEnable.name: zhnDhcpServerEnable
zhnDhcpServerEnable.description: Enables or disables the DHCP server on the LAN interface.

dhcpRelay.name: dhcpRelay
dhcpRelay.description: Indicates if the DHCP server performs the role of a server or a relay on the LAN interface.

minAddress.name: minAddress
minAddress.description: Specifies first address in the pool to be assigned by the DHCP server on the LAN interface.

maxAddress.name: maxAddress
maxAddress.description: Specifies last address in the pool to be assigned by the DHCP server on the LAN interface.

reservedAddresses.name: reservedAddresses
reservedAddresses.description: Comma separated list of addresses marked reserved from the address allocation pool.

dnsServers.name: dnsServers
dnsServers.description: Comma separated list of DNS servers offered to DHCP clients. Support for more than three DNS Servers is Optional.

domainName.name: domainName
domainName.description: Sets the domain name to provide to clients on the LAN interface.

ipRouters.name: ipRouters
ipRouters.description: Comma separated list of IP addresses of routers on this subnet. Also known as default gateway. Support for more than one Router address is Optional.

dhcpLeaseTime.name: dhcpLeaseTime
dhcpLeaseTime.description: Specifies the lease time in seconds of client assigned addresses. A value of -1 indicates an infinite lease.

ipInterfaceNumberOfEntries.name: ipInterfaceNumberOfEntries
ipInterfaceNumberOfEntries.description: Number of IP interface at LAN side of the CPE. 1 is a typical value for CPE not supporting Multihomed interfaces. Support for more than one interface instance is Optional.

ipInterfaceIPAddress.name: ipInterfaceIPAddress
ipInterfaceIPAddress.description: IP address of the LAN-side interface of the CPE.

ipInterfaceSubnetMask.name: ipInterfaceSubnetMask
ipInterfaceSubnetMask.description: Subnet mask of the LAN-side interface of the CPE.

ipInterfaceAddressingType.name: ipInterfaceAddressingType
ipInterfaceAddressingType.description: Represents the addressing method used to assign the LAN-side IP address of the CPE on this interface of the CPE. Enumeration of: DHCP Static Auto-IP

ipInterfaceifName.name: ipInterfaceifName
ipInterfaceifName.description: The interface name for this LAN device.

firewallEnabled.name: firewallEnabled
firewallEnabled.description: Indicates if a stateful firewall is enabled for all traffic from this IP interface to the modem. If TRUE, all inbound local traffic (from LAN to modem) that is not responding to an outbound packet or listed in the firewall exception table will be blocked.

defaultGateway.name: defaultGateway
defaultGateway.description: The IP address of the default gateway for this IP interface. This parameter is configurable only if the AddressingType is Static.

natEnabled.name: natEnabled
natEnabled.description: This parameter enables or disables NAT for this IP interface. This parameter is configurable only if this interface is on an uplink port.

dhcpcPid.name: dhcpcPid
dhcpcPid.description: If the address type is DHCP, then we will start a DHCP client to get the IP address for this IP interface. The process ID (pid) is stored in this field. A pid of 0 indicates that no dhcpc is running.

dnsType.name: dnsType
dnsType.description: This object specifies the DNS mode for this IP interface. The DNS associates hostname-to-IP address, and so domain names and IP addresses can be used interchangeably. Enumeration of: Default - Get the DNS information from the uplink interface Static - The DNSinformation is manually provisioned DHCP - The DNS information is obtained via DHCP

primaryDnsIPAddress.name: primaryDnsIPAddress
primaryDnsIPAddress.description: The DNS server primary IP address.

secondaryDnsIPAddress.name: secondaryDnsIPAddress
secondaryDnsIPAddress.description: The DNS server secondary IP address.

zhnVlanType.name: zhnVlanType
zhnVlanType.description: This object specifies the VLAN connection type of the interface.

connectionType.name: connectionType
connectionType.description: This object specifies the connection type of the interface.

maxMTUSize.name: maxMTUSize
maxMTUSize.description: The maximum size of IP packet that can be transmitted without fragmentation - including IP headers but excluding headers from lower levels in the protocol stack. The default MTU size is 1500 bytes.

alternateWanIfName.name: alternateWanIfName
alternateWanIfName.description: Name of a different VLAN WAN interface to run on if the current VLAN WAN interface is set to unconfigured.

naptEnabled.name: naptEnabled
naptEnabled.description: This parameter enables or disables NAPT for this IP interface. This parameter is configurable only if this interface is on an uplink port.

pppoeConfigTable.name: pppoeConfigTable
pppoeConfigTable.description: PPPoE configuration interface table for LAN interfaces.

pppoeIfName.name: pppoeIfName
pppoeIfName.description: The interface name for this LAN device.

pid.name: pid
pid.description: This object holds the process id (pid) of the pppd associated with this connection. A pid of 0 indicates that there is no pppd running.

connectionRequest.name: connectionRequest
connectionRequest.description: This object is used to bring up or down a PPPoE connection. Enumeration of: None Down Up Connect Disconnect

username.name: username
username.description: PPP requires that you have a user name and password to establish your connection. This object is the login user name to be used for PPP authentication.

password.name: password
password.description: PPP requires that you have a user name and password to establish your connection. This object is the login password to be used for PPP authentication. When read, this parameter returns an empty string, regardless of the actual value.

authentication.name: authentication
authentication.description: This object is the PPP authentication protocol to be used for PPP authentication. Enumeration of: AUTO_AUTH PAP CHAP MS-CHAP

serviceName.name: serviceName
serviceName.description: This object is the PPP Service Name. It should be filled only if specified by the provider.

encryptionProtocol.name: encryptionProtocol
encryptionProtocol.description: This object describes the PPP encryption protocol. Enumeration of: None MPPE

compressionProtocol.name: compressionProtocol
compressionProtocol.description: This object describes the PPP compression protocol used between the WAN device and the ISP POP. Enumeration of: None VanJacobsen STAC-LZS

idleDisconnectTime.name: idleDisconnectTime
idleDisconnectTime.description: The time in seconds that if the connection remains idle, the CPE automatically terminates the connection. A value of 0 (zero) indicates that the connection is not to be shutdown automatically.

holdOffTime.name: holdOffTime
holdOffTime.description: Set time in seconds before retrying connection.

useStaticIpAddress.name: useStaticIpAddress
useStaticIpAddress.description: If TRUE, PPPoE connection will use a static IP address.

pppoeStatusTable.name: pppoeStatusTable
pppoeStatusTable.description: PPPoE configuration interface table for LAN interfaces.

connectionStatus.name: connectionStatus
connectionStatus.description: Current status of the PPP connection.

lastConnectionError.name: lastConnectionError
lastConnectionError.description: The failure reason of the last PPP connection setup.

connectionEstablishedTime.name: connectionEstablishedTime
connectionEstablishedTime.description: The last time the PPP connection was established.

currentMTUSize.name: currentMTUSize
currentMTUSize.description: The current MTU in use over this connection.

uptime.name: uptime
uptime.description: The time in seconds this connection has been up.

zhnDhcpConditionalServingPoolTable.name: zhnDhcpConditionalServingPoolTable
zhnDhcpConditionalServingPoolTable.description: A collection of configuration parameters for DHCP conditional serving.

dhcpPoolChaddr.name: dhcpPoolChaddr
dhcpPoolChaddr.description: MAC address of the physical interface of the DHCP client. A perfect match is needed. An empty value indicates this criterion is not used for conditional serving.

dhcpPoolChaddrMask.name: dhcpPoolChaddrMask
dhcpPoolChaddrMask.description: Chaddr is only to be done for bit positions set to one in the mask. A mask of FF:FF:FF:FF:FF:FF indicates all bits of the Chaddr are to be used for classification. A perfect match is needed. An empty value indicates this criterion is not used for conditional serving.

dhcpPoolMinAddress.name: dhcpPoolMinAddress
dhcpPoolMinAddress.description: Specifies first address in the pool to be assigned by the DHCP server on the LAN interface.

dhcpPoolMaxAddress.name: dhcpPoolMaxAddress
dhcpPoolMaxAddress.description: Specifies last address in the pool to be assigned by the DHCP server on the LAN interface.

dhcpPoolReservedAddresses.name: dhcpPoolReservedAddresses
dhcpPoolReservedAddresses.description: Comma separated list of addresses marked reserved from the address allocation pool.

dhcpPoolSubnetMask.name: dhcpPoolSubnetMask
dhcpPoolSubnetMask.description: Specifies the clients network subnet mask.

dhcpPoolDnsServers.name: dhcpPoolDnsServers
dhcpPoolDnsServers.description: Comma separated list of DNS servers offered to DHCP clients. Support for more than three DNS Servers is Optional.

dhcpPoolDomainName.name: dhcpPoolDomainName
dhcpPoolDomainName.description: Sets the domain name to provide to clients on the LAN interface.

dhcpPoolIPRouters.name: dhcpPoolIPRouters
dhcpPoolIPRouters.description: Comma separated list of IP addresses of routers on this subnet. Also known as default gateway. Support for more than one Router address is Optional.

dhcpPoolLeaseTime.name: dhcpPoolLeaseTime
dhcpPoolLeaseTime.description: Specifies the lease time in seconds of client assigned addresses. A value of -1 indicates an infinite lease.

dhcpPoolUseWanVlan.name: dhcpPoolUseWanVlan
dhcpPoolUseWanVlan.description: The WAN VLAN is used to determine the default gateway router for upstream packets that have a source IP address in this subnet. A zero value indicates that the WAN VLAN is not used.

dhcpPoolEnableStaticLease.name: dhcpPoolEnableStaticLease
dhcpPoolEnableStaticLease.description: Enable this option to permanently bind the IP address to the client MAC.

dhcpPoolRowStatus.name: dhcpPoolRowStatus
dhcpPoolRowStatus.description: The SNMP RowStatus of the current row. The following object must be specified upon row creation: dhcpPoolChaddr

lanEthernetInterfaceConfigTable.name: lanEthernetInterfaceConfigTable
lanEthernetInterfaceConfigTable.description: Table of LAN ethernet interface configuration objects. This object models an Ethernet LAN connection on a CPE device. This object must be implemented for all CPEs that contain an Ethernet interface on the LAN side.

lanEthernetInterfaceConfigEntry.name: lanEthernetInterfaceConfigEntry
lanEthernetInterfaceConfigEntry.description: Table entry for LAN ethernet interface configuration objects.

lanEthernetStatus.name: lanEthernetStatus
lanEthernetStatus.description: Indicates the status of this interface. Enumeration of: Up NoLink Error Disabled

macAddress.name: macAddress
macAddress.description: ASCII representation of the physical address of the interface

macAddressControlEnabled.name: macAddressControlEnabled
macAddressControlEnabled.description: Indicates whether MAC Address Control is enabled or not on this interface. MAC Address Control limits the clients that connect to those that match a list of allowed MAC addresses specified in InternetGatewayDevice.LANDevice.{i}.LANHostConfigManagement.AllowedMACAddresses.

maxBitRate.name: maxBitRate
maxBitRate.description: The maximum upstream and downstream bit rate available to this connection. Enumeration of: 10 100 1000 Auto

duplexMode.name: duplexMode
duplexMode.description: The duplex mode available to this connection. Enumeration of: Half Full Auto

zhnIfName.name: zhnIfName
zhnIfName.description: Ethernet interface name such as eth0, eth1.

zhnEthernetPriorityMark.name: zhnEthernetPriorityMark
zhnEthernetPriorityMark.description: 802.1P priority value for this ethernet interface. Assigment of priority values is done via the Layer 2 Bridge Marking Table. Therefore, this object is read-only.

dot1qPvid.name: dot1qPvid
dot1qPvid.description: Default 802.1Q VLAN ID for this ethernet interface.

lanEthernetAlias.name: lanEthernetAlias
lanEthernetAlias.description: A descriptive name for this ethernet interface.

pauseMode.name: pauseMode
pauseMode.description: The pause mode available to this connection. Enumeration of: Auto Enable Disable

lanEthernetAcl.name: lanEthernetAcl
lanEthernetAcl.description: The access list values available to an ethernet interface. Enumeration of: Disable BlackList WhiteList Unsupported

lanEthernetAclRulesNumberofEntries.name: lanEthernetAclRulesNumberofEntries
lanEthernetAclRulesNumberofEntries.description: The number of entries in the access list table for this ethernet interface.

lanEthernetLanFollowsWan.name: lanEthernetLanFollowsWan
lanEthernetLanFollowsWan.description: Enable or disable this LAN interface based upon the WAN status.

lanEthernetIgmpPriorityMark.name: lanEthernetIgmpPriorityMark
lanEthernetIgmpPriorityMark.description: The 802.1P priority value that this LAN interface will assign to ingress untagged IGMP frames.

lanEthernetIgmpPvid.name: lanEthernetIgmpPvid
lanEthernetIgmpPvid.description: The VLAN ID that this LAN interface will assign to ingress untagged IGMP frames.

lanEthIntfStatisticsTable.name: lanEthIntfStatisticsTable
lanEthIntfStatisticsTable.description: Table of LAN ethernet interface statistics objects. This object contains statistics for an Ethernet LAN connection on a CPE device.

lanEthIntfStatisticsEntry.name: lanEthIntfStatisticsEntry
lanEthIntfStatisticsEntry.description: Table entry for LAN ethernet interface statistics objects.

bytesSent.name: bytesSent
bytesSent.description: Total number of bytes sent over the interface since the CPE was last reset.

bytesReceived.name: bytesReceived
bytesReceived.description: Total number of bytes received over the interface since the CPE was last reset.

packetsSent.name: packetsSent
packetsSent.description: Total number of packets sent over the interface since the CPE was last reset.

packetsReceived.name: packetsReceived
packetsReceived.description: Total number of packets received over the interface since the CPE was last reset.

txErrors.name: txErrors
txErrors.description: Total number of transmit errors on the interface since the CPE was last reset.

rxErrors.name: rxErrors
rxErrors.description: Total number of receive errors on the interface since the CPE was last reset.

txDrops.name: txDrops
txDrops.description: Total number of packets dropped on the transmit side of the interface since the CPE was last reset.

rxDrops.name: rxDrops
rxDrops.description: Total number of packets dropped on the receive side of the interface since the CPE was last reset.

lanEthIntfStatusTable.name: lanEthIntfStatusTable
lanEthIntfStatusTable.description: Table of LAN ethernet interface status objects. This object models an Ethernet LAN connection on a CPE device. This object must be implemented for all CPEs that contain an Ethernet interface on the LAN side.

lanEthIntfStatusEntry.name: lanEthIntfStatusEntry
lanEthIntfStatusEntry.description: Table entry for LAN ethernet interface status objects.

rateStatus.name: rateStatus
rateStatus.description: The port's current maximum bit rate.

lanEthIntfRateLimitTable.name: lanEthIntfRateLimitTable
lanEthIntfRateLimitTable.description: Table of LAN ethernet interface configuration objects. This object models an Ethernet LAN connection on a CPE device. This object must be implemented for all CPEs that contain an Ethernet interface on the LAN side.

lanEthIntfRateLimitEntry.name: lanEthIntfRateLimitEntry
lanEthIntfRateLimitEntry.description: Rate limit table entry for LAN ethernet interface configuration objects.

rateLimitEnable.name: rateLimitEnable
rateLimitEnable.description: This object is used to enable or disable rate limit on a port. Setting it to True will rate limit traffic on the port to a specified peak rate.

peakRate.name: peakRate
peakRate.description: This object identifies the maximum rate (0-1000) in Mbps on a port. If Rate Limit is disabled, this object has no effect.

burstSize.name: burstSize
burstSize.description: This object burst size. If Rate Limit is disabled, this object has no effect.

rateDirection.name: rateDirection
rateDirection.description: This object specifies the traffic direction to which the rate limit applies. The supported values are inbound, outbound or both. If the Rate Limit is disabled, this object has no effect.

inboundPeakRate.name: inboundPeakRate
inboundPeakRate.description: This object identifies the maximum rate (0-1000) in Mbps on a port for inbound data. If Rate Limit is disabled, this object has no effect.

igmpGroupsTable.name: igmpGroupsTable
igmpGroupsTable.description: Table of IGMP Multicast Groups currently detected by IGMP snooping.

igmpGroupAddress.name: igmpGroupAddress
igmpGroupAddress.description: This object identifies the IP address of the multicast group.

igmpGroupReporterIP.name: igmpGroupReporterIP
igmpGroupReporterIP.description: This object identifies the IP address of the host in the multicast group.

igmpGroupReporterMAC.name: igmpGroupReporterMAC
igmpGroupReporterMAC.description: This object identifies the MAC address of the host in the multicast group.

igmpGroupInterface.name: igmpGroupInterface
igmpGroupInterface.description: This object identifies the interface that discovered the multicast group.

igmpGroupVlan.name: igmpGroupVlan
igmpGroupVlan.description: This object identifies the VLAN that discovered the multicast group.

igmpGroupExpiration.name: igmpGroupExpiration
igmpGroupExpiration.description: This object identifies the time (in seconds) before the multicast group times out.

igmpGroupQuerier.name: igmpGroupQuerier
igmpGroupQuerier.description: This object identifies the IP address to be used by a proxy querier.

lanDefaultIfIpAddress.name: lanDefaultIfIpAddress
lanDefaultIfIpAddress.description: The IP address of the default interface, as configured by IPInterfaceIPAddress.

lanEthAclRulesTable.name: lanEthAclRulesTable
lanEthAclRulesTable.description: Table of LAN ethernet access list rules. This table contains a list of all access rules used to filter incoming traffic for a single physical ethernet interface.

lanEthAclRulesEntry.name: lanEthAclRulesEntry
lanEthAclRulesEntry.description: Table entry for LAN ethernet access list objects.

lanAclRuleKey.name: lanAclRuleKey
lanAclRuleKey.description: Index for the Ethernet Access List table.

lanAclRuleName.name: lanAclRuleName
lanAclRuleName.description: The user defined identifier for the rule. When creating a new rule, this field must be provided and must be unique per interface rule.

lanAclRuleSourceIPAddress.name: lanAclRuleSourceIPAddress
lanAclRuleSourceIPAddress.description: The Source IP address to filter. The address may include a subnet prefix length in CIDR notation. Therefore the format would be 192.168.2.0/24. This is a ASCII representation of the IP address

lanAclRuleSourceMACAddress.name: lanAclRuleSourceMACAddress
lanAclRuleSourceMACAddress.description: The Source MAC Address to filter. ASCII representation of the physical address of the interface

lanAclRuleSourceMACMask.name: lanAclRuleSourceMACMask
lanAclRuleSourceMACMask.description: Mask by which to filter MAC address. For example a MAC Mask of ff:ff:ff:00:00:00 would filter against the first six digits of the MAC address. ASCII representation of the MAC Mask

lanAclRuleRowStatus.name: lanAclRuleRowStatus
lanAclRuleRowStatus.description: The SNMP RowStatus of the current row. The following object must be specified upon row creation: lanAclRuleName

zhnLANDeviceCompliance.name: zhnLANDeviceCompliance
zhnLANDeviceCompliance.description: The Compliance statement for SNMP entities which manage the Zhone CPE LAN Device Information

zhnLANDeviceGroup.name: zhnLANDeviceGroup
zhnLANDeviceGroup.description: A collection of Zhone LAN Device objects that describe the LAN interfaces of the device.

zhnLANIgmpSnoopingGroup.name: zhnLANIgmpSnoopingGroup
zhnLANIgmpSnoopingGroup.description: A collection of Zhone LAN Device objects that describe the IGMP snooping capabilities of the device.

zhnLANHostConfigManagementGroup.name: zhnLANHostConfigManagementGroup
zhnLANHostConfigManagementGroup.description: A collection of Zhone LAN Host Configuration Management objects that describe the LAN IP addressing of the device.

zhnIpInterfaceGroup.name: zhnIpInterfaceGroup
zhnIpInterfaceGroup.description: A collection of Zhone LAN IP Address objects that describe the IP connectivity of interfaces of the device.

zhnPPPoEConfigGroup.name: zhnPPPoEConfigGroup
zhnPPPoEConfigGroup.description: A collection of Zhone LAN PPPoE objects that describe the configuration of PPPoE connections for interfaces of the device.

zhnPPPoEStatusGroup.name: zhnPPPoEStatusGroup
zhnPPPoEStatusGroup.description: A collection of Zhone LAN PPPoE objects that describe the status of PPPoE connections for interfaces of the device.

zhnLANEthernetInterfaceConfigGroup.name: zhnLANEthernetInterfaceConfigGroup
zhnLANEthernetInterfaceConfigGroup.description: A collection of Zhone LAN Ethernet objects that describe the ethernet-like interfaces of the device.

zhnLANEthIntfStatisticsGroup.name: zhnLANEthIntfStatisticsGroup
zhnLANEthIntfStatisticsGroup.description: A collection of Zhone LAN Ethernet objects that convey statistical information for the ethernet-like interfaces of the device.

zhnLANEthIntfStatusGroup.name: zhnLANEthIntfStatusGroup
zhnLANEthIntfStatusGroup.description: A collection of Zhone LAN Ethernet objects that convey the status of the ethernet-like interfaces of the device.

zhnLANEthIntfRateLimitGroup.name: zhnLANEthIntfRateLimitGroup
zhnLANEthIntfRateLimitGroup.description: A collection of Zhone LAN Ethernet objects that convey the rate-limit information of the ethernet-like interfaces of the device.

zhnLANIGMPMulticastGroup.name: zhnLANIGMPMulticastGroup
zhnLANIGMPMulticastGroup.description: A collection of Zhone LAN IGMP objects that identify the multicast groups currently detected by IGMP snooping within the device.

zhnLANSystemGroup.name: zhnLANSystemGroup
zhnLANSystemGroup.description: A collection of Zhone LAN System-wide scalar objects that identify the system default interface.

zhnLANAclRulesGroup.name: zhnLANAclRulesGroup
zhnLANAclRulesGroup.description: A collection of Zhone LAN Ethernet interface access-list rules with which to filter incoming traffic.

zhnDhcpConditionalServingPoolGroup.name: zhnDhcpConditionalServingPoolGroup
zhnDhcpConditionalServingPoolGroup.description: A collection of configuration parameters for DHCP conditional serving.
